## Analysis and Assembly Instructions:

1.  **Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

    *   **Block Count & Layers:** The structure consists of 14 blocks and is constructed in 4 layers.
    *   **Spatial Relationships:**
        *   Layer 1 consists of two red arch blocks (index 2).
        *   Layer 2 has the following:
            *   Two yellow half-cylinder blocks (index 12) on top of the left red arch.
            *   One green rectangular block (index 9) and one yellow rectangular block (index 10) on top of the right red arch.
            *   One green rectangular block (index 7) and one yellow rectangular block (index 11) on top of the middle red arch.
        *   Layer 3 has the following:
            *   One green rectangular block (index 8) on top of the green rectangular block (index 9).
            *   One yellow rectangular block (index 11) on top of the yellow rectangular block (index 10).
            *   One blue rectangular block (index 3) on top of a green rectangular block (index 6) and a red arch block (index 2).
        *   Layer 4:
            *   One orange triangle block (index 16) on top of the blue block.

2.  **Select the Required Blocks from the Dictionary:**

    *   Block Indices:
        *   2, 2, 2, 12, 12, 10, 11, 9, 7, 8, 11, 3, 6, 16
